						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying on the north side of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14 • • , Dhātu,</hi> the other details being lost.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a temple and the consecration of the image of Hanumān therein by Veṁgalappa, son of a <hi rend="italic">rāyasam,</hi> whose name is lost.</p>						

